    <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
      <head>Biographical History</head>
      <p>Joseph Golden was an American writer and professor in the College of Visual and Performing Arts at Syracuse University.</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
      <head>Scope and Contents of the Collection</head>
      <p>The <emph render="bold">Joseph Golden Papers</emph> comprise two series: Miscellaneous and Writings.  <emph render="bold">Miscellaneous</emph> contains a memo to Golden from a colleague at Syracuse Unviersity.  <emph render="bold">Writings</emph> contains the working manuscript of Golden's book, <emph render="italic">The Death of Tinkerbell: The American Theatre in the Twentieth Century</emph>, correspondence about a speaking engagement at which he presented a paper entitled "Death of the Left in the Thirties," and typescripts of plays and television scripts which he authored.</p>
    </scopecontent>
